verbose_text: Trapping of the CAP domain within the cell wall through a GPI anchored nanobody results in a dose dependent inhibition of mating, suggesting that a membrane proximal CAP domain inhibits a key step in the mating reaction, which is possibly related to the function of CAP domain proteins in mammalian fertilization.
